body: Nature, Published online: 12 November 2025; doi:10.1038/s41586-025-09704-6 In flowering plants, DNA–FD–14-3-3 recruits FT to the florigen activation complex both through DNA–FT interactions and by reducing liquid phase condensation of FD protein, which promotes dimerization, leading to FT recruitment.

body: Nature, Published online: 12 November 2025; doi:10.1038/d41586-025-03644-x In the development of large-scale quantum processors, material improvements yield rapid progress because they can be readily translated to many devices and platforms.
